# Protocol 26: Agent Proceed Confirmation (AGENT-PROCEED-CONF)

> **Normative:** `gtcx-docs/governance/protocols/26-agent-proceed-confirmation/protocol.md` (v1.1.0)
> **Phase:** 5.6 (after P22 selection)

## Rule

After `pnpm agent:next-work`, emit **one Proceed Brief**, then **implement**. Human may **stop**, **correct**, or name a story ID — never pick among agent-generated options.

## Proceed Brief (required)

```markdown
## Proceed Brief

**Next:** <single action from agent:next-work>
**Because:** <P22 selection.reason>
**Blocked until:** <none | artifact>
**Override:** stop | correct: | story ID
```

## Hard-forbidden replies (never send)

- Your call / Your call on …
- Two options / 1. … 2. … (story, repo, or sprint menus)
- Since blockers are done, natural transition point → menu
- Either IR-X in infra or switch to compliance-os now
- Which do you prefer? / What would you like me to do next?
- Do you want me to work on A or B?
- Say push if you want / push queue + ask (push yourself — P27)
- **Say if you want** / committed next or / left as local WIP (commit Class R yourself)
- Approval of path already chosen via P22 (Class R — proceed)

## Status Update (end of turn — required)

After substantive work, use **Status Update** (Execution mode → Done → Next work item → Approval needed). See `.cursor/rules/agent-mandatory-closing.mdc`. Never end with only a summary table + a question.

## When P22 returns a story

Execute **that story in this repo**. Do not offer a parallel repo unless P24 records a blocker and P22 selects handoff.

## With P27

Run commands yourself after the brief — no terminal delegation.
